---
description: Go test conventions
globs:
  - "**/*_test.go"
---
When editing Go test files in this repository:

- Use `github.com/stretchr/testify` for assertions (`assert` and `require`).
- Keep tests deterministic; avoid network and time dependencies when possible.
- Use `t.Parallel()` for independent tests.
- Use `t.TempDir()` for temporary directories; never write outside it.
- Follow `gofmt` style; run `gofmt -l .` before finishing.
- Run `go test ./...` to verify.
